author: jerenkrantz
msg: ra_serf: first-cut at REPORT parsing implementation and driving the WC.
We can now drive a checkout and write the files to the WC, but the props aren't
written correctly and we won't traverse sub-directories yet.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_serf.c
(report_state_e): Add a state enum to help us keep track of our progress as
we parse the REPORT response.
(report_info_t): Store info for the current state shared with fetch_t and
state_list_t.
(report_fetch_t): Context for a single file fetch
(report_state_list_t): state/info-tuple
(report_context_t): add in namespace list, base revision, state list, and
active fetches list.
(push_state): advance to a new parsing state.
(pop_state): go back to the previous parsing state.
(handle_fetch): take a fetched response and feed it to the WC
(walk_all_props): visitor function that walks all properties.
(set_file_props): function that calls WC change_file_prop for one prop
(fetch_file): fetch a file from scratch and deliver into WC
(start_report, end_report, cdata_report): parse update-report responses
(finish_report): keep calling context_run until we clear out pending fetches
(svn_ra_serf__do_update): init active_fetches
